ZH: 我家的炉子很旧了，需要换一个新的。
EN: My stove at home is very old and needs to be replaced.

ZH: 炉子上的火很旺，烧得菜很好吃。
EN: The fire on the stove is strong, making the dishes taste delicious.

ZH: 这个炉子有自动断电功能，非常安全。
EN: This stove has an automatic power-off function, very safe.

ZH: 她正在炉子上烤蛋糕。
EN: She is baking a cake on the stove.

ZH: 我不小心碰到炉子，烫伤了手。
EN: I accidentally touched the stove and burned my hand.

ZH: 我准备在炉子上煮汤。
EN: I am going to cook soup on the stove.

ZH: 炉子上的火烧得太大了，快点调小火。
EN: The fire on the stove is too strong, quickly turn it down.

ZH: 我喜欢在炉子旁边取暖。
EN: I like to warm up by the stove.

ZH: 这个炉子可以同时煮两锅菜。
EN: This stove can cook two dishes at the same time.

ZH: 没有瓦斯了，炉子无法使用。
EN: There is no gas, the stove cannot be used.

ZH: 她把锅放在炉子上，开始煮饭。
EN: She put the pot on the stove and started cooking.

ZH: 炉子的温度太低，煮不熟饭。
EN: The temperature of the stove is too low, the rice cannot be cooked properly.

ZH: 这个炉子的火力调节很方便。
EN: The fire adjustment of this stove is very convenient.

ZH: 我在炉子上炖了一锅排骨汤。
EN: I stewed a pot of spare ribs soup on the stove.

ZH: 她站在炉子旁边煎牛排。
EN: She stood by the stove and fried the steak.

ZH: 炉子上的火烧得太小，煮东西需要很长时间。
EN: The fire on the stove is too low and it takes a long time to cook things.

ZH: 我喜欢用电炉子，因为更方便控制温度。
EN: I prefer using an electric stove because it is easier to control the temperature.

ZH: 这个炉子的火烧得太慢，不适合快炒菜。
EN: The fire on this stove burns too slowly and is not suitable for stir-frying.

ZH: 我家的炉子是电磁炉，加热很快。
EN: My stove at home is an induction cooker, it heats up quickly.

ZH: 炉子上的灶眼坏了，需要修理。
EN: The burner on the stove is broken and needs to be repaired.
